1
00:00:59,017 --> 00:01:00,086
Yan!

2
00:01:00,777 --> 00:01:02,927
That's enough! Stop!

3
00:01:04,657 --> 00:01:05,931
Stop it!

4
00:01:22,017 --> 00:01:27,375
MAY 2002
SIX MONTHS BEFORE YAN'S DEATH

5
00:01:34,697 --> 00:01:36,813
Do you know what "messed up" means?

6
00:01:37,057 --> 00:01:41,926
The first masseuse that came in
looked exactly like Sam's dog

7
00:01:42,177 --> 00:01:44,213
so I asked for a replacement.

8
00:01:44,457 --> 00:01:47,051
The next one that came in
was even worse.

9
00:01:47,297 --> 00:01:49,174
She looked identical to Sam.

10
00:01:49,417 --> 00:01:52,966
Can you imagine?
Even I couldn't handle that.

11
00:01:53,257 --> 00:01:57,250
She had the audacity to ask me if she
was pretty. Of course I said no.

12
00:01:57,497 --> 00:01:59,010
Then she clawed me.

13
00:01:59,257 --> 00:02:00,372
So I called you.

14
00:02:00,617 --> 00:02:01,845
That's when we messed up.

15
00:02:02,097 --> 00:02:05,567
You smashed the whole place up.
It'll cost me a fortune in damages.

16
00:02:05,817 --> 00:02:08,854
So if a masseuse is ugly,
you're definitely screwed.

17
00:02:12,337 --> 00:02:15,090
Why are you swearing at your boss?

18
00:02:16,417 --> 00:02:18,692
Nurse, it's not sore, is it?

19
00:02:20,057 --> 00:02:21,172
Yan...

20
00:02:22,017 --> 00:02:25,009
I asked you to do a small job.
You don't have to be like that.

21
00:02:25,857 --> 00:02:28,769
You moan
that I don't give you anything to do.

22
00:02:29,017 --> 00:02:31,292
You don't need to work
in this business.

23
00:02:31,537 --> 00:02:34,131
If you want to work,
why don't you go and be a cop?

24
00:02:36,497 --> 00:02:39,330
Do you know why
I've only got you under my wing?

25
00:02:40,057 --> 00:02:42,890
It's because
I like that you're focused.

26
00:02:43,137 --> 00:02:44,855
It's important to be focused.

27
00:02:45,097 --> 00:02:47,486
Look at Sam. He's focused, isn't he?

28
00:02:47,737 --> 00:02:50,046
As for what happened today...

29
00:02:50,297 --> 00:02:51,810
Don't let Sam know.

30
00:02:52,057 --> 00:02:55,845
Ever since his wife died, he hates us
going to massage parlours.

31
00:02:56,417 --> 00:02:57,770
Why don't you let me go?

32
00:02:58,017 --> 00:02:59,769
Are you done talking? Get inside.

33
00:03:00,017 --> 00:03:02,167
Hey, don't push me, Officer.

34
00:03:02,417 --> 00:03:03,896
That's not the way to behave.

35
00:03:04,137 --> 00:03:06,093
Even cops shouldn't be like that.

36
00:03:06,777 --> 00:03:08,927
So are you going to tell on me?

37
00:03:09,177 --> 00:03:10,087
That's enough.

38
00:03:10,337 --> 00:03:14,535
That's life. Either you get me or I
get you. Are you going to tell on me?

39
00:03:14,777 --> 00:03:16,256
- Fuck off!
- Don't fight!

40
00:03:16,497 --> 00:03:18,055
You're hitting your own boss?

41
00:04:43,337 --> 00:04:48,013
OCTOBER 2003
TEN MONTHS AFTER YAN'S DEATH

42
00:04:48,257 --> 00:04:50,373
File number IO143 -

43
00:04:50,617 --> 00:04:53,927
regarding the deaths of 27149,
Officer Chan Wing Yan

44
00:04:54,177 --> 00:04:58,090
and 34689, Officer Lam Gok Ping.

45
00:04:58,737 --> 00:05:02,047
Internal Affairs
have produced the following report.

46
00:05:02,297 --> 00:05:04,686
On November 26th 2002,

47
00:05:04,977 --> 00:05:06,649
Senior Inspector Lau Kin Ming of IA

48
00:05:06,937 --> 00:05:10,373
contacted undercover officer,
Chan Wing Yan.

49
00:05:10,617 --> 00:05:13,529
With help from Officer Chan

50
00:05:13,777 --> 00:05:17,406
and from the OCTB unit
in West Kowloon,

51
00:05:17,657 --> 00:05:19,648
Lau toppled Sam's drug operation

52
00:05:19,897 --> 00:05:23,572
and cocaine
worth HK$60 million was seized.

53
00:05:23,817 --> 00:05:26,092
On November 27th 2002,

54
00:05:26,337 --> 00:05:29,170
Officer Chan met with Inspector Lau,

55
00:05:29,417 --> 00:05:31,533
on the rooftop
of the Sei Fong Centre.

56
00:05:31,817 --> 00:05:34,251
Yan supplied information
on triad moles.

57
00:05:36,537 --> 00:05:38,050
You can't get away.

58
00:05:38,297 --> 00:05:39,252
Just wait and see.

59
00:05:41,897 --> 00:05:43,455
You're going to kill a cop?

60
00:05:47,577 --> 00:05:50,296
I know all about you and Sam.

61
00:05:50,537 --> 00:05:52,732
You have no choice.
Come back with me.

62
00:05:53,017 --> 00:05:53,972
Drop your gun.

63
00:05:59,097 --> 00:06:01,053
- What do you want?
- I want to get away.

64
00:06:13,257 --> 00:06:17,535
The preceding testimony was provided
by Senior Inspector Lau Kin Ming.

65
00:06:17,777 --> 00:06:20,086
The committee
of two Chief Superintendents

66
00:06:20,577 --> 00:06:22,488
and the Assistant Commissioner

67
00:06:22,777 --> 00:06:25,007
unanimously believe Lau's testimony.

68
00:06:25,297 --> 00:06:28,255
Inspector Lau's killing

69
00:06:28,537 --> 00:06:32,450
of Officer Lam Kok Ping
has been ruled legal.

70
00:06:32,937 --> 00:06:37,772
Lam has been confirmed as a mole
sent by Sam into the police force.

71
00:06:38,457 --> 00:06:39,936
Finally, it's all over.

72
00:06:43,217 --> 00:06:44,286
You all believe me?

73
00:06:44,537 --> 00:06:45,936
It's all over.

74
00:06:46,937 --> 00:06:48,416
Stay in Admin for now, OK?

75
00:06:51,057 --> 00:06:52,046
Wait.

76
00:06:53,817 --> 00:06:54,772
Got it.

77
00:06:55,017 --> 00:06:57,736
Your parking space -
wait three weeks. That's it.

78
00:06:58,497 --> 00:06:59,407
Bye.

79
00:07:00,297 --> 00:07:01,650
Officer Chan.

80
00:07:01,937 --> 00:07:03,609
Hold on.

81
00:07:04,937 --> 00:07:07,690
Your uniform's ready.
Come and get it if you're free.

82
00:07:07,937 --> 00:07:09,689
Or I can send it over to you.

83
00:07:10,617 --> 00:07:12,847
No problem! OK. Bye.

84
00:07:13,097 --> 00:07:15,452
It's a shame Lam destroyed the CCTV.

85
00:07:15,697 --> 00:07:17,415
It's dragged on for so long.

86
00:07:17,657 --> 00:07:20,125
You know
our bosses go on accountability.

87
00:07:20,377 --> 00:07:23,289
Luckily, you're one of us.
It was all sorted quickly.

88
00:07:24,137 --> 00:07:25,968
You can come back to IA next month.

89
00:07:26,737 --> 00:07:27,965
Are you tired?

90
00:07:28,217 --> 00:07:30,572
If you are, you should go
on holiday with Mary.

91
00:07:31,617 --> 00:07:32,652
Hello.

92
00:07:42,617 --> 00:07:43,527
OK.

93
00:07:46,257 --> 00:07:48,009
I'll sign the documents tomorrow.

94
00:07:50,017 --> 00:07:50,927
OK.

95
00:07:52,057 --> 00:07:53,376
We can split it.

96
00:07:54,577 --> 00:07:56,090
We can split it.

97
00:08:00,737 --> 00:08:02,534
We can split anything but the baby!

98
00:08:12,137 --> 00:08:13,365
Hello, Officer Chan,

99
00:08:14,577 --> 00:08:15,692
your uniform's ready.

100
00:08:15,937 --> 00:08:18,053
If you're busy, I can send it over.

101
00:08:18,897 --> 00:08:21,775
I can do it. OK, wait for me. Bye.

102
00:09:05,537 --> 00:09:07,334
Have I done something wrong?

103
00:09:10,497 --> 00:09:12,374
I feel like beating someone up today.

104
00:09:17,137 --> 00:09:19,651
What's with all the fuss,
Superintendent Yeung?

105
00:09:23,377 --> 00:09:26,175
These Taiwanese men are arms dealers.

106
00:09:27,217 --> 00:09:29,777
Their customers haven't shown up.

107
00:09:31,297 --> 00:09:33,857
They seemed bored,
so I'm keeping them company.

108
00:09:34,457 --> 00:09:35,367
OK?

109
00:09:35,657 --> 00:09:36,931
Sure.

110
00:09:39,657 --> 00:09:41,010
I work in the Security Wing.

111
00:09:42,937 --> 00:09:45,656
I don't like to see
respectable people coming here.

112
00:09:46,497 --> 00:09:48,727
You've got lots of men here.
Help me out.

113
00:09:50,857 --> 00:09:52,176
That's difficult for me.

114
00:09:57,297 --> 00:09:59,208
Would this make it better?

115
00:09:59,457 --> 00:10:01,413
What? You want to set me up?

116
00:10:11,537 --> 00:10:12,731
Is that better?

117
00:10:13,537 --> 00:10:15,971
We've already written the report.

118
00:10:16,217 --> 00:10:18,685
That's half a kilo.
Minimum eight to ten years.

119
00:10:35,097 --> 00:10:37,088
Get two of your men
to come back with me.

120
00:10:38,377 --> 00:10:39,776
They're going to say

121
00:10:40,017 --> 00:10:42,577
they saw them take out some drugs.

122
00:10:43,777 --> 00:10:46,337
Being good citizens,
they beat them up.

123
00:10:48,377 --> 00:10:51,096
I'll give them a Good Citizen Award.

124
00:10:51,897 --> 00:10:52,852
How about that?

125
00:10:53,697 --> 00:10:54,607
Good.

126
00:10:55,457 --> 00:10:56,367
Arrest them.

127
00:10:58,297 --> 00:10:59,207
Be polite.

128
00:11:15,017 --> 00:11:17,133
Sir, you can't go in.

129
00:11:20,217 --> 00:11:21,206
Step aside.

130
00:11:23,497 --> 00:11:24,725
Over there.

131
00:11:25,417 --> 00:11:27,055
Yeung Kam Wing, don't go too far.

132
00:11:27,297 --> 00:11:28,935
I've helped you all these years.

133
00:11:31,337 --> 00:11:32,531
Do you want me dead?

134
00:11:49,297 --> 00:11:51,652
If I go down,
you'll suffer the consequences.

135
00:11:52,777 --> 00:11:55,007
Won't you give me a chance?

136
00:12:08,817 --> 00:12:12,014
ONE MONTH LATER

137
00:12:57,857 --> 00:12:59,290
Delivery from OCTB?

138
00:13:01,457 --> 00:13:06,451
I was transferred from OCTB yesterday
along with the coffee.

139
00:13:06,697 --> 00:13:07,652
Have a seat.

140
00:13:08,857 --> 00:13:10,370
I've given coffee up.

141
00:13:10,617 --> 00:13:13,575
I need sleeping pills
to get to sleep these days.

142
00:13:14,537 --> 00:13:16,129
I can't sleep if I drink coffee.

143
00:13:20,217 --> 00:13:24,256
Life is so unpredictable. I used
to really hate Internal Affairs.

144
00:13:24,937 --> 00:13:26,814
And now, I've been transferred here.

145
00:13:29,337 --> 00:13:33,012
You don't seem to be very happy.
I can transfer you elsewhere.

146
00:13:35,577 --> 00:13:36,692
Are you kidding?

147
00:13:36,937 --> 00:13:38,655
I moved here because of you.

148
00:13:39,817 --> 00:13:41,296
The files are on your desk.

149
00:13:42,257 --> 00:13:43,406
The first file...

150
00:13:43,657 --> 00:13:47,013
This sergeant killed himself
in front of his ex-boss, Yeung.

151
00:13:48,497 --> 00:13:50,931
Internal Affairs
is working on a few big cases.

152
00:13:52,297 --> 00:13:55,095
You know Security are very political.

153
00:13:55,777 --> 00:13:57,529
Everything is classified there.

154
00:13:57,817 --> 00:14:00,809
They won't answer
any questions you ask.

155
00:14:01,057 --> 00:14:03,696
We found a letter
on Sergeant Chun's desk.

156
00:14:03,937 --> 00:14:05,689
There was a tape inside.

157
00:14:05,937 --> 00:14:08,405
It was a conversation
between him and Sam.

158
00:14:08,657 --> 00:14:10,852
It turns out he was Sam's mole too.

159
00:14:11,537 --> 00:14:15,325
Besides him, several officers have
also committed suicide or vanished.

160
00:14:15,577 --> 00:14:17,488
They were all Sam's moles.

161
00:14:17,737 --> 00:14:19,489
The bosses say, after Sam's death,

162
00:14:19,737 --> 00:14:22,615
one of the moles is killing
the others to keep his cover.

163
00:14:22,857 --> 00:14:25,815
Leung has ordered us
to find out who he is.

164
00:14:26,057 --> 00:14:27,490
Do you know what happened?

165
00:14:28,417 --> 00:14:31,853
A package was sent to Leung.
Guess what it contained.

166
00:14:34,737 --> 00:14:36,648
It had tapes of us
giving tips to Sam.

167
00:14:38,497 --> 00:14:40,533
Luckily,
Sergeant Chun was one of us.

168
00:14:40,777 --> 00:14:43,769
- How many more of us are there?
- Five, including you.

169
00:14:51,257 --> 00:14:53,327
Ronald, this is Inspector Lau.

170
00:14:54,297 --> 00:14:55,855
I've left something at Admin.

171
00:15:01,537 --> 00:15:03,016
Hello?

172
00:15:03,257 --> 00:15:06,294
I've found out something on Chun.

173
00:15:06,537 --> 00:15:08,209
He was in the Police Bowling Team.

174
00:15:08,457 --> 00:15:09,367
Wait.

175
00:15:09,617 --> 00:15:11,892
- That's what you asked for.
- Good.

176
00:15:12,137 --> 00:15:13,047
Thanks.

177
00:15:14,097 --> 00:15:15,007
Go on.

178
00:15:15,257 --> 00:15:17,088
He practised at the Lam Wah club.

179
00:15:17,337 --> 00:15:19,567
He rented his flat
from Gam Dok Investments,

180
00:15:19,817 --> 00:15:21,489
which owns three big properties.

181
00:15:21,737 --> 00:15:23,728
The owner is Shen, a Mainlander.

182
00:15:23,977 --> 00:15:26,172
I'll e-mail you
the information later.

183
00:15:26,977 --> 00:15:28,296
No, send it to me now.

184
00:15:35,457 --> 00:15:37,971
29TH FLOOR, DRAGON VIEW
GARDEN, BROADCAST DRIVE

185
00:15:42,857 --> 00:15:45,849
Inspector Lau, I'm Yeung Kam Wing
from Security Wing.

186
00:15:46,137 --> 00:15:47,775
I applied for a parking space.

187
00:15:48,017 --> 00:15:48,927
Let me check.

188
00:15:49,177 --> 00:15:50,496
I've waited a whole month.

189
00:15:50,737 --> 00:15:53,615
I don't want to bother you,
but will it take much longer?

190
00:15:53,897 --> 00:15:56,365
Sorry, but I've moved back to IA.

191
00:15:58,497 --> 00:16:01,887
I know,
but Admin asked me to contact you.

192
00:16:03,017 --> 00:16:05,850
Your application's
been approved for a month.

193
00:16:06,097 --> 00:16:08,736
Here. Your parking space is B3A6.

194
00:16:09,657 --> 00:16:12,012
We haven't been able
to reach you for a week.

195
00:16:12,257 --> 00:16:13,849
I've been off for a month.

196
00:16:14,097 --> 00:16:16,008
You know IA is investigating me.

197
00:16:16,257 --> 00:16:19,010
- I know.
- Are you investigating Admin today?

198
00:16:20,137 --> 00:16:21,855
No, I'm just picking up a uniform.

199
00:16:23,217 --> 00:16:25,572
That's a sergeant's uniform,
Inspector.

200
00:16:30,097 --> 00:16:32,657
The man who killed himself
in front of you wore it.

201
00:16:32,897 --> 00:16:34,774
I'm taking it back for investigation.

202
00:16:36,097 --> 00:16:37,576
Isn't the case closed now?

203
00:16:37,817 --> 00:16:40,251
Yes, or you wouldn't be back
from your break.

204
00:16:40,497 --> 00:16:41,930
- Thanks.
- You're welcome.

205
00:16:42,177 --> 00:16:43,326
B3A6.

206
00:16:52,137 --> 00:16:53,536
Have we met before?

207
00:16:54,177 --> 00:16:55,087
No.

208
00:16:56,577 --> 00:16:59,296
Do you know someone called Shen?

209
00:17:00,737 --> 00:17:01,806
No.

210
00:17:02,057 --> 00:17:04,366
Mind your own business.

211
00:17:06,857 --> 00:17:10,406
We found these photos
inside Chun's bowling locker.

212
00:17:11,817 --> 00:17:13,409
That's Shen in the photo.

213
00:17:14,297 --> 00:17:16,447
He used to be Sam's business partner.

214
00:17:16,697 --> 00:17:19,928
The man facing him
is Security Wing's Yeung.

215
00:17:20,217 --> 00:17:22,367
He's connected
to the sergeant's death.

216
00:17:22,617 --> 00:17:25,085
I think Yeung could be the mole.

217
00:18:32,937 --> 00:18:33,847
Hello?

218
00:18:39,417 --> 00:18:40,327
See you later.

219
00:19:02,697 --> 00:19:06,531
You're a good person. You come
and see him the moment you get back.

220
00:19:10,057 --> 00:19:11,126
You're a good man.

221
00:19:12,737 --> 00:19:16,366
If it wasn't for you,
he wouldn't be buried as a cop.

222
00:19:20,017 --> 00:19:21,336
It was my duty.

223
00:19:24,017 --> 00:19:25,609
I don't know why I helped him.

224
00:19:27,297 --> 00:19:29,447
I only knew him
for about five months.

225
00:19:29,697 --> 00:19:31,096
I've only seen him 21 times.

226
00:19:31,337 --> 00:19:33,851
HE DIED BRAVELY
HIS NOBLE SPIRIT IS ETERNAL

227
00:19:35,497 --> 00:19:36,896
He was a good cop.

228
00:19:38,617 --> 00:19:40,289
Anyone would have helped him.

229
00:19:50,497 --> 00:19:51,646
I'll give you a lift.

230
00:20:13,297 --> 00:20:14,252
Hello.

231
00:20:15,617 --> 00:20:16,936
I'm back.

232
00:20:17,857 --> 00:20:19,006
Let's get started.

233
00:20:27,737 --> 00:20:30,126
There are no triads in China.

234
00:20:34,857 --> 00:20:37,087
What China needs is wealth.

235
00:20:38,137 --> 00:20:41,493
Triads are all about life and death.
Business is all about money.

236
00:20:41,737 --> 00:20:44,092
Today, we're here to talk business.

237
00:20:46,857 --> 00:20:49,496
- But I'm a real triad.
- No.

238
00:20:50,257 --> 00:20:53,329
To me, you're the best businessman.

239
00:20:54,137 --> 00:20:55,616
My brother said so too.

240
00:20:56,857 --> 00:20:59,212
We have HK$100 million to spend.

241
00:20:59,457 --> 00:21:01,334
We want to invest in your business.

242
00:21:02,737 --> 00:21:04,853
We'll ask no questions.

243
00:21:05,097 --> 00:21:06,655
It's one country, two systems.

244
00:21:07,617 --> 00:21:12,054
As long as money breeds money,
we'll let you have full control.

245
00:21:12,977 --> 00:21:14,296
You still believe in that?

246
00:21:17,537 --> 00:21:20,574
You won't be able
to refuse our Mainland ties.

247
00:21:20,817 --> 00:21:24,207
You think a Hong Kong triad can
outlive a Mainland businessman?

248
00:21:25,737 --> 00:21:29,855
Without my brother's connections,
your business in China won't last.

249
00:21:36,377 --> 00:21:39,733
Sam, you're a Buddhist, right?

250
00:21:41,457 --> 00:21:43,049
Amitabha.

251
00:21:49,217 --> 00:21:51,606
Is the feng shui good here?

252
00:21:51,857 --> 00:21:53,768
The best in Hong Kong.

253
00:21:55,217 --> 00:21:57,970
I want to get
a longevity tablet here.

254
00:21:59,457 --> 00:22:00,572
For whom?

255
00:22:03,497 --> 00:22:04,566
For my wife.

256
00:22:06,177 --> 00:22:09,214
She died six months ago.

257
00:22:12,057 --> 00:22:14,696
And also one for myself.

258
00:22:18,497 --> 00:22:20,488
That's a small matter,
I'll handle it.

259
00:22:21,177 --> 00:22:22,769
- A small matter?
- Yes.

260
00:22:23,937 --> 00:22:26,770
If it's such a small matter,
let my men deal with it.

261
00:22:27,777 --> 00:22:29,495
We'll see how they handle it.

262
00:22:31,737 --> 00:22:32,726
Goodbye.

263
00:22:33,457 --> 00:22:34,492
Bye.

264
00:22:45,577 --> 00:22:46,805
Keung.

265
00:22:48,097 --> 00:22:49,815
You'll deal with his men.

266
00:22:50,737 --> 00:22:52,136
Are you kidding, Sam?

267
00:22:52,977 --> 00:22:55,411
I'm an idiot.
Do you want it messed up?

268
00:23:02,977 --> 00:23:04,933
What does that laugh mean?

269
00:23:38,057 --> 00:23:40,093
Excuse me. Thank you.

270
00:23:49,657 --> 00:23:50,612
That's a lot.

271
00:23:51,377 --> 00:23:52,730
Are you jealous?

272
00:23:52,977 --> 00:23:54,933
Is it legit? Be careful.

273
00:23:56,057 --> 00:23:57,934
Don't worry, boss.

274
00:23:58,177 --> 00:24:00,213
You know how much money I have.

275
00:24:00,937 --> 00:24:03,895
Just ask if you want a loan.
You don't need to threaten me.

276
00:24:06,057 --> 00:24:08,810
- What's this?
- It's for your baby daughter.

277
00:24:10,377 --> 00:24:12,732
You're a dad now.
You should go home more.

278
00:24:12,977 --> 00:24:14,012
Don't work so hard.

279
00:24:16,537 --> 00:24:19,290
You've lost weight recently.

280
00:24:19,577 --> 00:24:21,488
None of your business. But thanks.

281
00:24:24,297 --> 00:24:25,525
Who are these two?

282
00:24:26,297 --> 00:24:27,969
I only know they're Mainlanders.

283
00:24:28,217 --> 00:24:29,206
Anything else?

284
00:24:35,337 --> 00:24:38,613
Shen was born in Taiyuan, Shanxi.
He's been in the army.

285
00:24:38,857 --> 00:24:42,566
He dealt in antiques. He started
from scratch, now he's loaded.

286
00:24:42,857 --> 00:24:44,370
He came to Hong Kong a year ago.

287
00:24:44,617 --> 00:24:48,212
His brother Liang joined him
and does all the dirty work.

288
00:24:48,457 --> 00:24:50,573
Sam wants to expand to the Mainland.

289
00:24:50,857 --> 00:24:53,496
- What did he want you to talk about?
- Cooperation.

290
00:24:54,537 --> 00:24:55,936
- Liang.
- Yan.

291
00:24:56,177 --> 00:24:57,576
Sit down.

292
00:24:57,817 --> 00:24:58,932
Are you by yourself?

293
00:24:59,177 --> 00:25:00,530
You too, Liang?

294
00:25:03,097 --> 00:25:05,531
We have lots of nightclubs in China.

295
00:25:06,217 --> 00:25:09,050
They're all protected
by local gang bosses.

296
00:25:11,097 --> 00:25:13,008
Influential people.

297
00:25:15,097 --> 00:25:18,726
Your goods can move around
our network easily.

298
00:25:20,617 --> 00:25:23,131
We have businesses in 11 cities.

299
00:25:27,257 --> 00:25:28,167
Excuse me.

300
00:25:30,817 --> 00:25:33,775
- Hello?
- Well, how's the talk so far?

301
00:25:34,017 --> 00:25:34,972
Not bad.

302
00:25:36,817 --> 00:25:38,535
See the ashtray in front of you?

303
00:25:39,777 --> 00:25:42,245
Pick it up and smash him with it.

304
00:25:49,617 --> 00:25:50,606
Hit him!

305
00:25:51,297 --> 00:25:53,208
Hit him in the head!

306
00:26:45,897 --> 00:26:47,410
I'm screwed.

307
00:26:47,657 --> 00:26:49,773
- What is it?
- Mary's pregnant.

308
00:26:50,977 --> 00:26:53,491
- Congratulations.
- But we're not married yet.

309
00:26:53,737 --> 00:26:55,807
- Get married then.
- Is that necessary?

310
00:26:56,057 --> 00:26:58,855
- Or she can have an abortion.
- We're already engaged.

311
00:26:59,097 --> 00:27:00,325
Hello?

312
00:27:00,577 --> 00:27:01,726
Got it.

313
00:27:01,977 --> 00:27:03,535
- We can go.
- Let's go.

314
00:27:08,057 --> 00:27:09,888
Long time no see, Wong.

315
00:27:10,137 --> 00:27:13,095
But I saw you last week
with a girl in China.

316
00:27:13,337 --> 00:27:14,895
You don't have to shout.

317
00:27:15,137 --> 00:27:17,367
Security people are full of secrets.

318
00:27:20,337 --> 00:27:21,326
Stop for a minute.

319
00:27:37,417 --> 00:27:39,135
Hey, what's going on?

320
00:27:39,417 --> 00:27:41,169
What are you doing here?

321
00:27:46,777 --> 00:27:49,689
Hey! What's going on?
What are you doing?

322
00:27:57,177 --> 00:27:58,292
Sorry, sir.

323
00:27:58,537 --> 00:28:02,291
We were asked to take some mugshots.
I don't know what's going on either.

324
00:28:03,097 --> 00:28:04,928
I asked CIB to open a file

325
00:28:05,937 --> 00:28:08,053
and take a picture of everyone.

326
00:28:09,017 --> 00:28:09,927
Is that alright?

327
00:28:12,977 --> 00:28:15,810
Officers, are you done?

328
00:28:17,617 --> 00:28:18,732
Everybody's here.

329
00:28:25,657 --> 00:28:27,932
We were investigating Mr Shen...

330
00:28:29,337 --> 00:28:32,374
...but we ended up
being led to Sam by chance.

331
00:28:33,137 --> 00:28:34,536
We even arrested Sam's men.

332
00:28:35,417 --> 00:28:37,487
I'll let CIB handle the triads.

333
00:28:37,737 --> 00:28:39,375
Sam, long time no see. Are you OK?

334
00:28:40,377 --> 00:28:44,165
- What brings you here?
- I'm accompanying some friends.

335
00:28:46,657 --> 00:28:49,171
You Hong Kong Police
are so inefficient.

336
00:28:50,417 --> 00:28:51,816
I'll speed it up then.

337
00:28:52,817 --> 00:28:54,887
He beat you up.

338
00:28:55,137 --> 00:28:56,616
Do you want to press charges?

339
00:28:56,897 --> 00:28:58,888
If not, then please sign here.

340
00:29:29,897 --> 00:29:31,649
I hit you. Want to press charges?

341
00:29:31,937 --> 00:29:33,052
You're crazy.

342
00:29:36,497 --> 00:29:38,533
Keung, let's go.

343
00:29:39,417 --> 00:29:40,327
Wait.

344
00:29:54,377 --> 00:29:55,935
Do you recognise me?

345
00:29:59,697 --> 00:30:02,336
I recognise you. Be careful.

346
00:30:07,217 --> 00:30:08,775
Wong.

347
00:30:09,577 --> 00:30:11,886
It's up to you what you do with them.

348
00:30:16,617 --> 00:30:18,209
It's OK. We all know each other.

349
00:30:31,057 --> 00:30:33,287
CIB colleagues, you can go now.

350
00:30:33,537 --> 00:30:35,050
Thanks, Ming. Thank you.

351
00:30:35,297 --> 00:30:36,696
Just doing my job.

352
00:30:36,937 --> 00:30:38,290
Let's go.

353
00:30:43,257 --> 00:30:44,212
What's your game?

354
00:30:45,857 --> 00:30:48,451
You think I'm playing?
It's life and death.

355
00:30:48,737 --> 00:30:49,806
I'm glad you know that.

356
00:31:07,217 --> 00:31:08,491
Hurry up and thank me.

357
00:31:08,737 --> 00:31:10,011
Thank you for what?

358
00:31:10,257 --> 00:31:12,725
- Look what you're doing.
- Eating.

359
00:31:12,977 --> 00:31:14,615
You're eating shark fin.

360
00:31:14,857 --> 00:31:16,495
Shark fin, think about it.

361
00:31:16,737 --> 00:31:20,446
When Sam took me to Thailand,
I had shark fin and then I moved up.

362
00:31:21,217 --> 00:31:23,685
You're having shark fin
so you're moving up.

363
00:31:23,937 --> 00:31:26,929
Sam's mean,
but he still bought you shark fin.

364
00:31:27,177 --> 00:31:28,405
Just think about it.

365
00:31:45,697 --> 00:31:46,607
Take him.

366
00:31:48,937 --> 00:31:49,926
Let go of him.

367
00:31:54,777 --> 00:31:55,812
Sam,

368
00:31:56,857 --> 00:31:58,973
are you letting them
take Yan to China?

369
00:32:00,377 --> 00:32:01,969
Ask him why he smashed his head.

370
00:32:07,257 --> 00:32:08,929
He smashed his head?

371
00:32:09,177 --> 00:32:10,087
That's nothing.

372
00:32:10,337 --> 00:32:12,897
In this job,
either you get them or they get you.

373
00:32:14,017 --> 00:32:17,566
Yan smashed his head, right?
How about this?

374
00:32:20,657 --> 00:32:22,170
Is that alright now?

375
00:32:31,057 --> 00:32:31,967
Liang.

376
00:32:36,897 --> 00:32:39,411
Are you here to make a scene...

377
00:32:40,657 --> 00:32:42,807
...or are you here for business?

378
00:32:48,697 --> 00:32:49,607
Go.

379
00:32:50,617 --> 00:32:51,527
Go!

380
00:32:58,217 --> 00:32:59,445
We're even now.

381
00:33:00,337 --> 00:33:01,816
Let's talk business.

382
00:33:05,177 --> 00:33:07,054
I heard
you have a big arms business.

383
00:33:07,337 --> 00:33:09,373
If you let me chip in...

384
00:33:11,977 --> 00:33:14,855
...the blood they have spilt
will not be in vain.

385
00:33:28,417 --> 00:33:29,532
Sam.

386
00:33:37,657 --> 00:33:38,646
So?

387
00:33:40,017 --> 00:33:41,291
You're not happy with me?

388
00:33:42,657 --> 00:33:43,567
No.

389
00:33:47,737 --> 00:33:49,170
Have you ever met someone...

390
00:33:50,577 --> 00:33:51,930
...who seems nice...

391
00:33:53,657 --> 00:33:55,454
...but who might kill you at any time?

392
00:33:59,497 --> 00:34:00,850
I've met someone like that.

393
00:34:05,297 --> 00:34:06,650
What do you think, Sam?

394
00:34:10,177 --> 00:34:11,496
I'm wondering...

395
00:34:13,257 --> 00:34:14,485
...why he didn't kill you.

396
00:34:18,857 --> 00:34:21,610
You'll look after
the Mainland business from now on.

397
00:34:24,537 --> 00:34:26,095
Take this for now.

398
00:34:42,617 --> 00:34:43,936
Shen's not what he seems.

399
00:34:44,177 --> 00:34:45,815
Security is investigating him.

400
00:34:46,777 --> 00:34:48,927
He could be smuggling arms.

401
00:34:49,177 --> 00:34:51,088
Sam stopped all his deals in China.

402
00:34:51,337 --> 00:34:53,214
They're going to work together soon.

403
00:34:53,457 --> 00:34:54,970
That's a big deal.

404
00:34:57,097 --> 00:34:58,450
What should I do?

405
00:34:59,177 --> 00:35:00,405
Have you seen the shrink?

406
00:35:01,217 --> 00:35:03,128
Why should I see a shrink?

407
00:35:03,377 --> 00:35:06,574
I persuaded the Department
of Justice not to send you to prison.

408
00:35:06,817 --> 00:35:11,174
It's fine if you don't want to go.
See you in prison. Bye.

409
00:35:12,337 --> 00:35:14,692
Hello? Hello? What's the address?

410
00:35:16,297 --> 00:35:17,207
Bye.

411
00:35:18,857 --> 00:35:20,370
I'm meeting with Dr Lee.

412
00:35:20,617 --> 00:35:21,527
This way.

413
00:36:32,137 --> 00:36:34,856
Are you planning
to spend the night here?

414
00:36:39,577 --> 00:36:41,374
I can't fall asleep in my office.

415
00:36:45,697 --> 00:36:46,686
Unlike him.

416
00:37:00,537 --> 00:37:02,095
He said...

417
00:37:03,697 --> 00:37:05,335
...ever since he became a mole...

418
00:37:09,017 --> 00:37:11,212
...he could only fall asleep here.

419
00:37:23,777 --> 00:37:24,892
I still remember...

420
00:37:27,697 --> 00:37:28,652
That night...

421
00:37:31,977 --> 00:37:34,411
He said everything
would be OK after tomorrow.

422
00:37:38,937 --> 00:37:40,689
And then he died.

423
00:38:00,617 --> 00:38:01,766
You're a doctor.

424
00:38:09,617 --> 00:38:12,450
Do you still have his file?

425
00:38:14,977 --> 00:38:18,174
He may be dead,
but he's still a patient.

426
00:38:23,737 --> 00:38:24,852
- Let's go.
- OK.

427
00:38:36,897 --> 00:38:39,855
THREE HOURS LATER

428
00:39:31,257 --> 00:39:35,011
We found a letter on Sergeant Chun's
desk. There was a tape inside.

429
00:39:35,257 --> 00:39:38,135
It was a conversation
between him and Sam.

430
00:39:38,777 --> 00:39:40,495
The bosses say, after Sam's death,

431
00:39:40,777 --> 00:39:43,575
one of the moles is killing
the others to keep his cover.

432
00:39:44,577 --> 00:39:46,533
He's connected to Chun's death.

433
00:39:47,377 --> 00:39:49,447
I think Yeung could be the mole.

434
00:42:00,337 --> 00:42:02,567
Do you understand what I said?

435
00:42:02,817 --> 00:42:03,727
Sorry.

436
00:42:04,857 --> 00:42:08,372
I won't sign it
if she doesn't come and meet me.

437
00:42:08,617 --> 00:42:09,572
Do you understand?

438
00:42:10,577 --> 00:42:11,487
OK.

439
00:42:27,697 --> 00:42:29,653
My wife and I
may be getting divorced.

440
00:42:31,217 --> 00:42:32,252
Did I scare you?

441
00:42:33,297 --> 00:42:34,207
Sorry.

442
00:42:35,017 --> 00:42:35,927
Be careful.

443
00:42:36,217 --> 00:42:37,252
Of what?

444
00:42:38,777 --> 00:42:41,610
Your car's next to mine.
I drive badly.

445
00:42:41,857 --> 00:42:44,291
If I scratch your car,
come and find me.

446
00:42:48,897 --> 00:42:51,252
I'm a good driver.
You don't have to worry.

447
00:43:37,937 --> 00:43:40,974
The Taiwanese we arrested
will be discharged next week.

448
00:43:41,217 --> 00:43:43,287
The Taiwan authorities
have no comment.

449
00:43:43,537 --> 00:43:46,256
The Mainland police
will come for extradition.

450
00:43:46,497 --> 00:43:48,135
I know their boss well.

451
00:43:48,377 --> 00:43:50,686
Stick to the plan and be careful.

452
00:43:50,937 --> 00:43:52,336
When they arrive,

453
00:43:52,577 --> 00:43:56,013
make them feel welcome and take
them out for dinner and shopping.

454
00:43:56,657 --> 00:43:58,454
How about a nightclub?

455
00:43:58,697 --> 00:44:00,016
Macau is better.

456
00:44:00,257 --> 00:44:02,088
You're not afraid of reporters?

457
00:44:02,337 --> 00:44:04,726
We can cover their heads with bags.

458
00:44:04,977 --> 00:44:07,696
- OK, you bring the bags.
- What are you like?

459
00:44:08,777 --> 00:44:10,176
Superintendent Yeung.

460
00:44:10,417 --> 00:44:12,885
It's Sergeant Chun's memorial
next week.

461
00:44:13,137 --> 00:44:15,173
We're all chipping in for a service.

462
00:44:31,537 --> 00:44:33,209
- Do it properly.
- Yes, sir.

463
00:44:33,457 --> 00:44:36,654
Back to the Mainland police.
Talk to the Macau guys tomorrow.

464
00:44:36,897 --> 00:44:40,685
Let them plan the evening.
I'll talk to them about security.

465
00:44:41,337 --> 00:44:44,568
If we don't plan, it'll be a mess.
Then we won't have a good time.

466
00:49:47,617 --> 00:49:49,448
Anything to add to your testimony?

467
00:49:51,137 --> 00:49:52,047
No.

468
00:49:53,017 --> 00:49:55,406
Call us any time
if you need anything.

469
00:49:55,977 --> 00:49:57,012
Thank you.

470
00:49:58,457 --> 00:49:59,810
- Are you done?
- Yes.

471
00:50:02,337 --> 00:50:04,692
- Is it OK if I touch things?
- Yes.

472
00:50:04,937 --> 00:50:06,006
OK, thank you.

473
00:50:10,257 --> 00:50:12,134
Is everything OK?

474
00:50:13,337 --> 00:50:14,895
It was like this when I came in.

475
00:50:16,697 --> 00:50:19,609
They stole some cash and watches.

476
00:50:20,897 --> 00:50:22,330
And the computer's gone.

477
00:50:25,297 --> 00:50:28,972
It's better this way.
I can start from scratch.

478
00:50:32,617 --> 00:50:34,414
But the computer's useless to them.

479
00:50:36,977 --> 00:50:38,729
I locked it with my password.

480
00:50:39,457 --> 00:50:42,051
They won't know
it's my licence plate number.

481
00:50:51,177 --> 00:50:53,532
Your eyes are all red.

482
00:50:54,297 --> 00:50:55,776
You haven't slept?

483
00:50:57,497 --> 00:51:00,011
I've been
following several cases for days.

484
00:51:01,377 --> 00:51:02,696
You should get some sleep.

485
00:51:08,057 --> 00:51:10,730
OK.
Everything will be OK after tomorrow.

486
00:51:12,417 --> 00:51:14,533
I'm off.
Call me if you need anything.

487
00:52:00,417 --> 00:52:01,327
Mr Chan.

488
00:52:02,657 --> 00:52:07,526
AUGUST 16TH 2002
THE FIRST SESSION

489
00:52:10,017 --> 00:52:12,372
Mr Chan, I'm Dr Lee.

490
00:52:12,617 --> 00:52:17,247
I'm obligated to tell you that you've
been ordered to undergo treatment.

491
00:52:18,137 --> 00:52:20,970
You should complete the treatment
in six months.

492
00:52:22,257 --> 00:52:25,135
After that,
I'll submit a report to the Court.

493
00:52:26,617 --> 00:52:29,370
The Court will use that
to decide if you should go to prison.

494
00:52:32,897 --> 00:52:33,807
Prison?

495
00:52:35,097 --> 00:52:36,530
Isn't the treatment enough?

496
00:52:37,217 --> 00:52:40,095
You must follow
doctor's orders during this time

497
00:52:40,337 --> 00:52:43,249
or the Court can revoke the sentence

498
00:52:43,497 --> 00:52:46,011
and detain you for handling.

499
00:52:46,257 --> 00:52:47,246
I see.

500
00:52:50,497 --> 00:52:51,896
Excuse me.

501
00:52:56,457 --> 00:52:58,095
Wong, you git.

502
00:53:01,577 --> 00:53:04,728
Dr Lee, you don't need
to call the police. Just call me.

503
00:53:04,977 --> 00:53:06,296
You have my mobile number.

504
00:53:11,657 --> 00:53:13,329
I'll become a wanted criminal.

505
00:53:13,577 --> 00:53:16,774
THE SECOND SESSION

506
00:53:22,577 --> 00:53:24,807
Mr Chan, I'm Dr Lee.

507
00:53:25,057 --> 00:53:29,175
I'm obligated to tell you that you've
been ordered to undergo treatment.

508
00:53:29,417 --> 00:53:32,136
You should complete the treatment
in six months.

509
00:53:32,377 --> 00:53:34,288
You'll submit a report to the Court.

510
00:53:34,537 --> 00:53:38,246
They'll use this report and they
might put me in prison. I get it.

511
00:53:39,217 --> 00:53:40,809
Please sign here then.

512
00:53:44,657 --> 00:53:46,773
We think you have a violent streak

513
00:53:47,057 --> 00:53:49,446
so we'll use hypnotism
for your treatment.

514
00:53:49,737 --> 00:53:50,453
Hypnotism?

515
00:53:52,377 --> 00:53:53,366
You signed the form.

516
00:53:54,057 --> 00:53:54,967
Hypnotism?

517
00:53:58,137 --> 00:53:59,490
You can refuse it

518
00:53:59,737 --> 00:54:01,455
but the Court can revoke it.

519
00:54:01,737 --> 00:54:03,170
And lock me up?

520
00:54:09,057 --> 00:54:10,172
Alright, then.

521
00:54:11,897 --> 00:54:12,807
Hypnotize me.

522
00:54:13,617 --> 00:54:14,970
Hypnotize me now.

523
00:54:16,897 --> 00:54:17,966
Let's begin.

524
00:54:19,297 --> 00:54:21,049
Please introduce yourself.

525
00:54:21,297 --> 00:54:22,810
Talk about your family.

526
00:54:27,177 --> 00:54:28,087
Mr Chan?

527
00:54:29,217 --> 00:54:30,127
Mr Chan.

528
00:54:32,057 --> 00:54:33,172
Can you cooperate?

529
00:54:33,817 --> 00:54:36,775
I was practising just in case
you couldn't hypnotize me.

530
00:54:37,017 --> 00:54:38,848
I can hypnotize myself for you.

531
00:54:40,017 --> 00:54:41,928
