He's gone.

662
01:07:07,657 --> 01:07:08,567
Who is he?

663
01:07:10,817 --> 01:07:11,727
A pimp.

664
01:07:13,297 --> 01:07:14,525
Why were you tailing him?

665
01:07:16,457 --> 01:07:18,971
I'm a pimp too.
I want to know if he stole my girls.

666
01:07:21,577 --> 01:07:23,727
Actually, I could do with some money.

667
01:07:24,697 --> 01:07:27,370
If you don't mind,
how about hiring me?

668
01:07:31,057 --> 01:07:32,331
Be serious, Dr Lee.

669
01:07:33,257 --> 01:07:34,849
Be serious, pimp.

670
01:08:04,337 --> 01:08:06,328
Hello, Internal Affairs.

671
01:08:06,577 --> 01:08:09,455
Boss, I saw Yeung with Sam today.

672
01:08:10,137 --> 01:08:12,651
Yeung may be a mole.
Run a check on him.

673
01:08:13,737 --> 01:08:16,456
Sam's deal with Shen
should start soon.

674
01:08:20,577 --> 01:08:21,487
Hello?

675
01:09:06,497 --> 01:09:08,135
Uncle Chan, you're here so late.

676
01:09:08,377 --> 01:09:10,095
I'm changing the water.

677
01:09:11,297 --> 01:09:13,174
You're quite something, Uncle Chan.

678
01:09:13,457 --> 01:09:15,573
You know exactly
when we run out of water.

679
01:09:15,817 --> 01:09:18,570
Don'tjust talk, give me a hand.

680
01:09:20,017 --> 01:09:21,370
Damon, help him.

681
01:09:24,377 --> 01:09:26,607
Let me, Uncle Chan. Let me.

682
01:09:54,537 --> 01:09:55,447
Hello?

683
01:09:55,697 --> 01:09:57,255
Why didn't you speakjust then?

684
01:09:58,497 --> 01:09:59,850
Yan sent me a tape.

685
01:10:03,457 --> 01:10:05,573
Chan Wing Yan sent you a tape?

686
01:10:11,577 --> 01:10:12,566
Wait for me.

687
01:10:16,457 --> 01:10:18,607
Hey! What's the matter with you?

688
01:10:18,857 --> 01:10:20,336
- I'm busy.
- Wait.

689
01:10:20,577 --> 01:10:21,612
What is it?

690
01:10:22,537 --> 01:10:24,368
You've been back for two days.

691
01:10:24,617 --> 01:10:27,177
You haven't seen anybody else but me.

692
01:10:28,257 --> 01:10:30,134
Am I supposed to greet everyone?

693
01:10:31,537 --> 01:10:32,447
Hey!

694
01:10:42,457 --> 01:10:43,412
Did I scare you?

695
01:10:44,537 --> 01:10:45,447
Sorry.

696
01:10:46,737 --> 01:10:47,726
Sorry.

697
01:10:56,057 --> 01:10:58,935
I don't know why you've
locked yourself up for two days.

698
01:10:59,177 --> 01:11:02,328
Whatever it is,
don't take everything on yourself.

699
01:11:08,697 --> 01:11:10,608
Everything will be OK after tomorrow.

700
01:11:14,937 --> 01:11:15,847
Lau.

701
01:11:22,537 --> 01:11:23,731
The door is over there.

702
01:11:50,577 --> 01:11:55,935
PO BOX 27149
CHAN WING YIN

703
01:11:57,497 --> 01:11:58,566
Let's give it to OCTB.

704
01:12:08,857 --> 01:12:10,176
Have you listened to it?

705
01:12:11,777 --> 01:12:12,687
No.

706
01:12:38,297 --> 01:12:40,492
Sam and Shen's transaction
is in two days.

707
01:12:40,737 --> 01:12:42,534
There'll be lots of arms and coke.

708
01:12:42,777 --> 01:12:44,688
I'll contact you before it starts.

709
01:12:44,937 --> 01:12:47,053
So Sam doesn't
completely trust you yet.

710
01:12:48,937 --> 01:12:50,131
Beware of Yeung.

711
01:12:50,857 --> 01:12:51,767
I will.

712
01:12:52,377 --> 01:12:53,776
Can you arrest him?

713
01:12:54,497 --> 01:12:55,691
You saw them together.

714
01:12:55,937 --> 01:12:58,007
That's not enough.
How can I arrest him?

715
01:12:59,257 --> 01:13:01,009
Boss, I'm risking my life for you.

716
01:13:01,257 --> 01:13:02,610
Don't tell me that.

717
01:13:03,337 --> 01:13:05,328
I'll take care of Yeung.

718
01:13:10,857 --> 01:13:11,767
You?

719
01:13:13,137 --> 01:13:14,934
Don't worry. Lau's a great help.

720
01:13:15,217 --> 01:13:18,209
What are you saying?
It's his fault that you die.

721
01:13:20,017 --> 01:13:21,336
It was an accident.

722
01:13:22,097 --> 01:13:23,212
Don't you want us dead?

723
01:13:23,497 --> 01:13:25,965
I just want to be a good man.

724
01:13:30,457 --> 01:13:31,856
Give me another chance?

725
01:13:36,297 --> 01:13:39,016
Sorry, I'm a cop.

726
01:14:38,537 --> 01:14:39,856
Are you OK?

727
01:14:42,417 --> 01:14:43,327
I'm OK.

728
01:14:45,057 --> 01:14:45,967
I'm OK.

729
01:15:05,457 --> 01:15:07,129
Do you know what you were doing?

730
01:15:07,817 --> 01:15:09,250
I know. So what?

731
01:15:13,297 --> 01:15:16,130
- Can you take me back to my office?
- Of course.

732
01:15:16,377 --> 01:15:18,686
Are you OK? Come on, let's go.

733
01:16:09,137 --> 01:16:10,047
Good morning.

734
01:16:18,577 --> 01:16:21,296
Your hypnotherapy is really good.

735
01:16:22,097 --> 01:16:23,291
I'm all relaxed.

736
01:16:24,497 --> 01:16:28,012
I've made some progress so I guess
I won't need to go to prison.

737
01:16:33,697 --> 01:16:37,656
We need to work together
in hypnotherapy.

738
01:16:39,657 --> 01:16:41,295
If you don't tell the truth...

739
01:16:42,537 --> 01:16:44,016
...no one can help you.

740
01:16:44,257 --> 01:16:45,929
I'm already very cooperative.

741
01:16:47,977 --> 01:16:50,696
It's OK if you don't
want to talk about the triads...

742
01:16:51,897 --> 01:16:53,171
...but when we're chatting,

743
01:16:53,417 --> 01:16:57,569
you still lie about what films
you like and what you like to eat.

744
01:17:01,057 --> 01:17:02,285
I don't understand.

745
01:17:04,217 --> 01:17:06,412
You're not me.
You wouldn't understand.

746
01:17:16,657 --> 01:17:20,286
God didn't mean
for our minds to keep secrets.

747
01:17:22,417 --> 01:17:24,612
I remember when I was a child...

748
01:17:25,617 --> 01:17:27,972
...I stole some chocolate
from a supermarket.

749
01:17:29,137 --> 01:17:32,254
A family-sized bar. A foot long.

750
01:17:33,537 --> 01:17:36,813
When I got to the till,
the manager caught me.

751
01:17:37,977 --> 01:17:40,650
I was scared and I just cried.

752
01:17:42,217 --> 01:17:43,491
The manager let me go.

753
01:17:45,217 --> 01:17:48,527
Later, I went to the supermarket
with my mum.

754
01:17:48,777 --> 01:17:50,290
I saw the manager again.

755
01:17:51,657 --> 01:17:54,296
I just felt him staring at me.

756
01:17:54,537 --> 01:17:55,765
I felt uneasy.

757
01:17:56,897 --> 01:17:59,331
My mum asked me what was wrong.

758
01:18:00,337 --> 01:18:02,089
I said the manager had molested me.

759
01:18:02,777 --> 01:18:04,005
My mum called the police.

760
01:18:04,257 --> 01:18:06,566
The police took the manager away.

761
01:18:07,337 --> 01:18:10,056
That manager never told on me.

762
01:18:11,977 --> 01:18:14,855
I never saw him again.

763
01:18:16,937 --> 01:18:18,336
When I went to university,

764
01:18:19,257 --> 01:18:21,009
I finally told this to a classmate.

765
01:18:24,697 --> 01:18:25,925
After I told the story,

766
01:18:27,137 --> 01:18:30,812
I felt like I had been reborn.

767
01:18:34,457 --> 01:18:36,175
Can I really start over again?

768
01:18:38,737 --> 01:18:39,931
Do you trust me?

769
01:18:42,577 --> 01:18:43,566
I do.

770
01:18:43,817 --> 01:18:44,932
I do.

771
01:18:46,697 --> 01:18:48,210
It'll be OK if you trust me.

772
01:18:50,337 --> 01:18:52,407
When did you join the triads?

773
01:18:53,617 --> 01:18:55,289
I didn't want to be in the triads.

774
01:18:58,057 --> 01:18:59,206
I want to be a good man.

775
01:19:01,617 --> 01:19:02,652
But...

776
01:19:04,857 --> 01:19:06,256
...I met Mary.

777
01:19:08,657 --> 01:19:09,726
Your wife?

778
01:19:12,537 --> 01:19:13,652
Sam's woman.

779
01:19:15,937 --> 01:19:17,450
Why am I saying this?

780
01:19:20,617 --> 01:19:23,575
You have to trust me
so I can hypnotize you.

781
01:19:23,817 --> 01:19:25,648
Then we can solve your problems.

782
01:19:28,897 --> 01:19:30,694
You can't solve my problems.

783
01:19:31,897 --> 01:19:33,888
My job
is to betray those close to me.

784
01:19:37,577 --> 01:19:39,215
I don't know when I can stop.

785
01:19:42,617 --> 01:19:43,845
I want to survive...

786
01:19:45,657 --> 01:19:47,648
...so I have
to betray those close to me.

787
01:19:49,937 --> 01:19:50,926
Actually, I'm a cop.

788
01:19:52,457 --> 01:19:53,367
I'm a cop.

789
01:20:01,257 --> 01:20:02,895
I don't want to be Sam's mole.

790
01:20:20,177 --> 01:20:21,326
Did I scare you?

791
01:20:23,697 --> 01:20:24,925
Sorry.

792
01:20:38,697 --> 01:20:41,370
Don't worry,
everything will be OK after tomorrow.

793
01:20:50,737 --> 01:20:52,932
Where were you?
The transaction's today.

794
01:20:53,217 --> 01:20:54,366
- Today?
- Yeah.

795
01:20:54,617 --> 01:20:55,686
I've been forgetful.

796
01:20:58,897 --> 01:20:59,852
Hand these out.

797
01:21:00,697 --> 01:21:01,686
Yan.

798
01:21:07,377 --> 01:21:08,776
You go in Shen's boat.

799
01:21:09,017 --> 01:21:11,008
Be careful. There are arms in there.

800
01:21:12,537 --> 01:21:13,970
If anything goes wrong...

801
01:21:14,217 --> 01:21:15,445
I know.

802
01:21:16,017 --> 01:21:17,848
You go with me to the dockyard.

803
01:21:26,217 --> 01:21:28,731
Shen and Sam's deal
is happening tonight.

804
01:21:28,977 --> 01:21:31,935
They might be heavily armed.
Wear bulletproof vests.

805
01:21:32,697 --> 01:21:34,415
The water police are standing by.

806
01:21:34,697 --> 01:21:36,767
Teams A and B,
get ready on the hill.

807
01:21:38,817 --> 01:21:40,011
Call the operation off.

808
01:21:41,497 --> 01:21:42,691
What are you saying?

809
01:21:43,377 --> 01:21:44,696
It's an order from the top.

810
01:21:51,297 --> 01:21:52,935
An order from the top or from you?

811
01:21:54,577 --> 01:21:55,771
I don't need to explain.

812
01:21:58,337 --> 01:22:01,568
I've been on Sam's trail for years.
What are your ties with him?

813
01:22:02,697 --> 01:22:04,415
This is Security's top secret.

814
01:22:04,657 --> 01:22:07,854
You can make a formal inquiry
to the Assistant Commissioner.

815
01:22:09,497 --> 01:22:11,374
- Call IA and check.
- Yes, sir.

816
01:22:21,697 --> 01:22:23,688
Just do what Yeung says.

817
01:22:23,937 --> 01:22:24,847
I won't.

818
01:22:25,097 --> 01:22:27,850
Wong,
this isn't as simple as you think.

819
01:22:28,097 --> 01:22:29,689
It's very simple for me, sir.

820
01:22:29,937 --> 01:22:31,734
My man is risking his life out there.

821
01:22:32,657 --> 01:22:36,650
Everybody in OCTB stays put. You're
under disciplinary investigation.

822
01:22:39,497 --> 01:22:40,930
What disciplinary issues?

823
01:22:41,817 --> 01:22:44,695
You don't follow orders.
That's a disciplinary issue.

824
01:22:51,497 --> 01:22:52,566
Where are you going?

825
01:22:54,177 --> 01:22:55,610
Back to my office, sir.

826
01:22:59,417 --> 01:23:00,896
You can go.

827
01:23:14,737 --> 01:23:16,295
- Tang.
- Yes.

828
01:23:16,537 --> 01:23:18,209
- Turn back.
- OK.

829
01:23:18,457 --> 01:23:20,095
Ask everyone to follow our car.

830
01:23:22,257 --> 01:23:25,567
Sam, Yan's doing the transaction.

831
01:24:43,457 --> 01:24:44,367
Hello?

832
01:24:44,617 --> 01:24:47,689
Your wife has agreed to meet you
this afternoon. Is that OK?

833
01:24:50,777 --> 01:24:52,369
Thank you. Thank you.

834
01:24:58,697 --> 01:25:01,655
The Mainlanders
will come in today for extradition.

835
01:25:01,897 --> 01:25:04,536
Make sure nothing goes wrong.
Be careful.

836
01:25:04,777 --> 01:25:07,655
- Damon and Fai, you stay here.
- OK.

837
01:25:08,177 --> 01:25:10,737
Set the channel to 34879. OK?

838
01:25:11,497 --> 01:25:13,886
- Tell Transportation we can go now.
- OK.

839
01:25:51,857 --> 01:25:52,767
Thank you.

840
01:27:17,097 --> 01:27:19,736
Inspector Lau,
are you having fun in my office?

841
01:28:36,817 --> 01:28:39,126
Everybody, get ready. Follow me.

842
01:28:41,017 --> 01:28:41,972
What's going on?

843
01:28:42,217 --> 01:28:44,094
We're having Yeung round for coffee.

844
01:28:47,817 --> 01:28:51,696
The Mainlanders are chatting inside.
They'll meet our boss in 15 minutes.

845
01:28:51,937 --> 01:28:53,416
Don't make any mistakes.

846
01:28:53,657 --> 01:28:55,727
Damon and Fai,
get the documents ready.

847
01:29:04,897 --> 01:29:05,966
Yeung Kam Wing.

848
01:29:06,937 --> 01:29:09,132
You're suspected
of conspiring with Sam.

849
01:29:09,377 --> 01:29:11,333
Please come back with us to IA.

850
01:29:13,657 --> 01:29:16,569
Inspector Lau,
do you know what you're doing?

851
01:29:16,857 --> 01:29:17,812
I know.

852
01:29:22,257 --> 01:29:23,326
I found a tape.

853
01:29:24,017 --> 01:29:25,814
What tape? I don't understand.

854
01:29:26,897 --> 01:29:28,296
Listen and you will.

855
01:29:54,737 --> 01:29:55,772
Where's Sam?

856
01:29:56,377 --> 01:29:57,571
Sam's not here yet?

857
01:30:18,377 --> 01:30:19,412
They're empty!

858
01:30:21,257 --> 01:30:22,167
Shen!

859
01:31:01,017 --> 01:31:03,451
The arms cost HK$10 million.
Give them back.

860
01:31:03,697 --> 01:31:05,335
Those Mainlanders are animals.

861
01:31:06,777 --> 01:31:09,496
- What if they're setting me up?
- Who told you that?

862
01:31:11,377 --> 01:31:12,776
My life told me so.

863
01:31:13,457 --> 01:31:14,731
What if you're wrong?

864
01:31:15,937 --> 01:31:18,167
Then I'll cooperate with them.

865
01:31:19,777 --> 01:31:21,733
But Yan's going to die either way?

866
01:31:23,337 --> 01:31:26,374
We're all risking our lives
in this business.

867
01:31:27,617 --> 01:31:29,050
I almost died twice.

868
01:31:29,897 --> 01:31:31,410
Sam, don't play games.

869
01:31:31,897 --> 01:31:33,125
Sam!

870
01:31:33,377 --> 01:31:35,447
I've only ever had one guy
work for me!

871
01:31:35,697 --> 01:31:37,653
How can you do this to me?

872
01:31:38,737 --> 01:31:40,170
What are you saying?

873
01:32:18,657 --> 01:32:19,646
Tell me.

874
01:32:21,777 --> 01:32:22,687
Tell me.

875
01:32:24,017 --> 01:32:25,211
Where are my goods?

876
01:32:25,857 --> 01:32:27,210
Where have you put them?

877
01:32:28,697 --> 01:32:30,016
Go and ask Sam yourself.

878
01:32:39,057 --> 01:32:42,652
Why didn't you shoot me in the head?

879
01:32:44,697 --> 01:32:45,607
I didn't aim.

880
01:32:45,897 --> 01:32:47,012
Stand up.

881
01:32:47,937 --> 01:32:49,211
Stand up!

882
01:33:00,337 --> 01:33:02,009
Are you two in this together?

883
01:33:05,057 --> 01:33:06,775
You two are in this together.

884
01:33:07,297 --> 01:33:09,253
Sorry, I'm a cop.

885
01:33:09,977 --> 01:33:11,251
Go ahead and shoot.

886
01:33:11,537 --> 01:33:13,095
It'll save me a bullet.

887
01:33:14,697 --> 01:33:17,052
What? Are you sure you're a cop?

888
01:33:17,857 --> 01:33:21,167
I am.
I got an "A" for writing reports.

889
01:33:21,937 --> 01:33:24,929
After I kill both of you,
I can write what I like.

890
01:33:42,337 --> 01:33:44,089
He's not really Sam's man.

891
01:33:53,337 --> 01:33:55,134
Then you're not really Shen.

892
01:34:11,097 --> 01:34:12,530
You're just in time.

893
01:34:13,537 --> 01:34:15,687
Listen with us. It's interesting.

894
01:34:22,377 --> 01:34:25,414
So you don't want to help me,
Inspector Lau?

895
01:34:25,657 --> 01:34:28,091
I do, but they're watching me.

896
01:34:28,337 --> 01:34:32,046
So you're not worried about me.
You're worried about yourself.

897
01:34:32,297 --> 01:34:33,650
Whatever you say.

898
01:34:35,417 --> 01:34:36,611
You deal with him.

899
01:34:38,177 --> 01:34:40,930
Give me three days.
I'll run a check and call you.

900
01:34:53,817 --> 01:34:54,772
Inspector Lau.

901
01:34:56,657 --> 01:35:00,366
Lau Kin Ming,
this is your last chance.

902
01:35:01,657 --> 01:35:02,931
Don't waste it.

903
01:35:09,977 --> 01:35:12,537
Lau Kin Ming, you're under arrest.

904
01:35:12,777 --> 01:35:16,247
Lau Kin Ming's over there! What are
you doing? What are you doing?

905
01:35:17,177 --> 01:35:20,249
We agreed to arrest him.
Why are you helping him?

906
01:35:20,497 --> 01:35:22,488
Yeung found this tape in your room.

907
01:35:22,737 --> 01:35:26,571
- What's the problem?
- That cop was following me.

908
01:35:27,417 --> 01:35:30,215
I'm in charge now.
Call me if you've got transactions.

909
01:35:30,457 --> 01:35:32,448
We got the goods
when we killed the cop.

910
01:35:33,217 --> 01:35:34,332
Cuff him.

911
01:35:35,097 --> 01:35:36,052
What are you doing?

912
01:35:36,337 --> 01:35:38,055
Move back! Sit down!

913
01:35:38,337 --> 01:35:39,770
Sit down! Move back!

914
01:35:40,057 --> 01:35:41,775
- Inspector Lau...
- Move back!

915
01:35:42,457 --> 01:35:43,685
Move back!

916
01:35:43,937 --> 01:35:45,006
What are you doing?

917
01:35:49,897 --> 01:35:51,125
I told you to be careful.

918
01:35:51,417 --> 01:35:52,611
Why should I be careful?

919
01:35:52,857 --> 01:35:55,417
Why? I'm a good man.
Why should I be careful?

920
01:35:55,697 --> 01:35:56,846
Why?

921
01:36:02,457 --> 01:36:03,731
I worked so hard.

922
01:36:05,497 --> 01:36:06,612
I helped you kill...

923
01:36:07,857 --> 01:36:09,051
...all of Sam's moles.

924
01:36:09,297 --> 01:36:13,688
Why can't you give me a chance?
Why can't you give me a chance?

925
01:36:13,937 --> 01:36:15,290
I only want to be a good man.

926
01:36:16,217 --> 01:36:17,536
I only want to be a good man.

927
01:36:18,457 --> 01:36:20,493
Why can't
you give me a chance? Why?

928
01:36:20,777 --> 01:36:22,608
Tell me!

929
01:36:23,777 --> 01:36:25,847
Sorry, I'm a cop.

930
01:36:32,977 --> 01:36:35,571
Sorry, I'm a cop.

931
01:36:37,177 --> 01:36:38,212
I'm a cop too!

932
01:37:36,377 --> 01:37:39,289
Are you sure
you won't go to the hospital?

933
01:37:40,577 --> 01:37:43,296
People like me can't go out
into the light.

934
01:37:44,657 --> 01:37:45,612
Same here.

935
01:37:46,457 --> 01:37:49,608
I'll get more credits if I bleed.
Did I cause you trouble?

936
01:37:49,897 --> 01:37:51,376
It's just a report.

937
01:37:52,857 --> 01:37:55,690
- Be careful when dealing with Sam.
- You too.

938
01:37:57,017 --> 01:37:58,530
It was Sam who set you up.

939
01:37:58,777 --> 01:38:00,847
You won't bump into me next time.

940
01:38:02,657 --> 01:38:04,887
Will we see each other again?

941
01:38:05,537 --> 01:38:07,971
- I'll pass.
- Speak Mandarin.

942
01:38:08,217 --> 01:38:10,447
I'm going to Beijing next week.
Come along.

943
01:38:11,497 --> 01:38:12,816
I'll quit after this.

944
01:38:15,297 --> 01:38:16,207
And you?

945
01:38:17,097 --> 01:38:19,008
I'm a mole,

946
01:38:19,737 --> 01:38:21,011
we don't have holidays.

947
01:38:23,617 --> 01:38:24,572
OK.

948
01:38:26,017 --> 01:38:28,326
See you. See you.

949
01:38:28,577 --> 01:38:31,774
You haven't told us yet.
What's your name?

950
01:38:34,097 --> 01:38:35,086
Name?

951
01:38:35,817 --> 01:38:36,852
I don't know.

952
01:38:37,097 --> 01:38:38,974
Just call me Shadow.

953
01:38:39,737 --> 01:38:41,011
That's so corny!

954
01:38:44,017 --> 01:38:45,211
It's time for me to go.

955
01:38:46,177 --> 01:38:49,567
You haven't answered me yet.
I asked you if you recognised me.

956
01:38:51,537 --> 01:38:53,334
At the cadet school in 1991,

957
01:38:53,577 --> 01:38:56,137
if you hadn't left,
I wouldn't have got the Award.

958
01:40:17,977 --> 01:40:21,208
Lau's been taken to the hospital.
He's still in critical condition.

959
01:40:21,417 --> 01:40:23,885
The bullet is in his brain.

960
01:40:24,577 --> 01:40:26,693
The doctors
say that even if he recovers,

961
01:40:26,937 --> 01:40:28,848
his brain will be severely damaged.

962
01:40:29,097 --> 01:40:31,736
His room is full
of information about the moles.

963
01:40:31,977 --> 01:40:34,775
The department
was covered by hidden cameras

964
01:40:35,017 --> 01:40:37,212
that were connected
to Yeung's computer.

965
01:41:00,737 --> 01:41:01,647
Hello?

966
01:41:04,377 --> 01:41:05,412
Mary?

967
01:41:06,777 --> 01:41:08,529
He won't be able to meet you.

968
01:41:33,737 --> 01:41:38,413
DECEMBER 2002
TEN DAYS AFTER YAN'S DEATH

969
01:41:50,017 --> 01:41:51,609
He's dead.

970
01:41:52,377 --> 01:41:53,969
What's the point?

971
01:41:58,417 --> 01:42:01,614
There are things we've got to do.

972
01:42:38,137 --> 01:42:40,207
Hey, you're right.

973
01:43:33,737 --> 01:43:35,056
Dr Lee,

974
01:43:35,897 --> 01:43:37,649
everything will be OK after today.

975
01:43:38,577 --> 01:43:41,455
I'll arrest Lau Kin Ming myself.

976
01:43:52,337 --> 01:43:55,454
ONE MONTH LATER

977
01:44:12,337 --> 01:44:13,895
I'm giving it back to you.

978
01:44:17,657 --> 01:44:19,329
He turned me into a cripple.

979
01:44:50,097 --> 01:44:51,735
Was he Yan's friend?

980
01:44:58,137 --> 01:45:00,935
They were in cadet school together.

981
01:45:05,177 --> 01:45:08,328
12 YEARS EARLIER

982
01:45:08,817 --> 01:45:11,570
You have to follow the rules
at cadet school.

983
01:45:11,817 --> 01:45:15,526
Those who break the rules will be
like him. They'll be expelled.

984
01:45:16,537 --> 01:45:18,732
Who wants to trade places with him?

985
01:45:22,457 --> 01:45:25,335
Yeung, congratulations
on getting the Award.

986
01:45:26,057 --> 01:45:28,571
Would he have got it
if he hadn't been expelled?

987
01:45:47,817 --> 01:45:49,250
Perhaps that's fate.

988
01:45:50,417 --> 01:45:53,136
Destiny is destiny.

989
01:45:54,777 --> 01:45:58,611
Men are changed by events,
not events by men.

990
01:46:01,697 --> 01:46:02,766
But these two men...

991
01:46:04,497 --> 01:46:06,374
...they have changed certain events.

992
01:46:11,537 --> 01:46:12,447
OK...

993
01:46:13,937 --> 01:46:15,575
Let bygones be bygones.

994
01:46:17,857 --> 01:46:19,609
Tomorrow is another day.

995
01:46:24,017 --> 01:46:24,972
Bye.

996
01:46:56,177 --> 01:47:00,614
SEVEN MONTHS LATER

997
01:47:30,137 --> 01:47:31,490
You're here?

998
01:48:00,097 --> 01:48:01,610
The baby can say "daddy" now.

999
01:48:31,897 --> 01:48:34,365
He shot me so I shot him back,
like a triad would.

1000
01:48:34,617 --> 01:48:36,892
NOVEMBER 2002
A WEEK BEFORE YAN'S DEATH

1001
01:48:37,137 --> 01:48:40,015
Stop having a go at me
and learn from Yeung.

1002
01:48:40,257 --> 01:48:41,212
Learn what?

1003
01:48:41,457 --> 01:48:43,175
Learn how to write a report.

1004
01:48:43,417 --> 01:48:45,612
If you've killed someone,
it's a big deal.

1005
01:48:45,857 --> 01:48:47,210
So it's OK if I got killed?

1006
01:48:48,417 --> 01:48:49,736
Send me a report.

1007
01:48:49,977 --> 01:48:51,490
I'll send you nothing.

1008
01:48:52,177 --> 01:48:53,292
What did you say?

1009
01:49:02,617 --> 01:49:04,369
- You can go.
- What?

1010
01:49:04,617 --> 01:49:06,733
- Lunchtime.
- I've just had breakfast.

1011
01:49:06,977 --> 01:49:09,696
Would you rather eat shit instead?

1012
01:49:19,017 --> 01:49:20,336
Excuse me.

1013
01:49:20,617 --> 01:49:21,845
What is it?

1014
01:49:23,617 --> 01:49:26,131
I'd like to try this stereo.

1015
01:49:37,577 --> 01:49:39,886
KSITIGARBHA SUTRA:

1016
01:49:40,137 --> 01:49:43,846
SUCH PEOPLE SHALL BE CAST
INTO THE NEVER-ENDING HELL

1017
01:49:44,097 --> 01:49:47,806
AND WILL SUFFER CONTINUOUSLY
FOREVER AND EVER

1018
01:49:48,057 --> 01:49:50,890
WITH NO MEANS OF ESCAPE.
